         </div>
         <div type="edition" xml:lang="la" xml:space="preserve">
            <div type="textpart" n="i"><ab>
               <lb n="1"/><foreign xml:lang="grc"><placeName nymRef="Λέπκις ἡ Μεγάλη">Λέπκις <w lemma="ὁ">ἡ</w> <w lemma="μέγας">μεγάλη</w></placeName> <w lemma="φιλέω">φιλῖ</w> <w>σε</w><placeName>Ῥώμη</placeName></foreign>
               </ab></div>
            <div type="textpart" n="ii"><ab><lb n="1"/><g type="palm"/> <persName type="divine" nymRef="Genius"><name type="cognomen" nymRef="Genius">Genio</name> <g type="palm"/>
               <lb n="2"/><w lemma="colonia">coloni1e</w>
               <lb n="3"/><g type="palm"/> <placeName nymRef="Lepcis Magna">Lepcis <g type="palm"/>
                  <lb n="4"/><w lemma="magnus">Magnae</w></placeName></persName>
                  <lb n="5"/><persName type="attested"><name nymRef="Crescentina">Crescentina</name></persName> <w lemma="facio"><expan><abbr>f</abbr><ex>ecit</ex></expan></w>
            </ab></div></div>
         <div type="apparatus">
            <listApp>
               <app loc="i.1">
                  <rdg resp="#irt1952"><note>Or perhaps <foreign xml:lang="grc">φιλησιρώμη</foreign></note></rdg>
               </app>
               <app loc="ii.5"><rdg resp="#irt1952"> Crescentinae. 
                  <note>The final letter could be read as E or as F: but a check on the stone shows that there is no stop before it (the photograph is misleading on this point).
               This is perhaps in favour of the IRT reading Crescentinae - presumably a municipal title.</note></rdg></app>
            </listApp>
         </div>
         <div type="translation" source="#irt2009" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Lepcis, the great <supplied reason="subaudible">city</supplied>; Rome loves you.</p>
            <p>To the genius of the colony of Lepcis Magna Crescentina</p></div>
         
         <div type="translation" source="#tantillo2010" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Leptis Magna ti ama, o Roma! Al Genio della colonia di Leptis Magna, Crescentina fece (?)</p></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>For the acclamation see Robert, loc.cit.</p>
